-mass instability for\nneutron stars. Additionally, our results suggest that oscillations between the\ntwo Quantum Chromodynamic phases could provide gravitational wave signals\nassociated with such phase transitions in core-collapse supernovae and white\ndwarf-neutron star mergers.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 May 2021 18:01:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-09"}
