ictions. The complex structure of\nneutron-rich fluorine isotopes offers a trove of information about the\nformation of the southern shore of the IOI through a subtle interplay of\ndeformation and continuum couplings driven by the occupation of the\nquasi-degenerate neutron shells $0d_{3/2}$ and $1p_{3/2}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 May 2021 18:38:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 25 Aug 2021 12:36:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-21"}
